Author: bogybogy#3962
Content:
The crypto community is fighting a proxy battle. They are ill-prepared, with few presentable allies to hold the line against impending forays by lawmakers. And the proxy has a serious PR and credibility problem.,When the push comes to shove, the noisemakers on social media, the losers who post daily bromides, the "whales," pump-and-dump group operators, and the like have zero pull and zero power. They can't help. If invited, they'd be an embarrassment.The best defense against overeager lawmakers is a healthy community, with lots of use cases and positive outcomes, and people with credentials singing the praises of societal change to come.Crucially, the voices calling for an outright ban on crypto will get stronger and start consolidating. 


The crypto community needs to get ahead of the curve here and assemble a better presence in DC and elsewhere.
